Generate minimum set solution

Source: R/fct_min_set_solution.R
min_set_solution.Rd

Create a new Solution object by generating a prioritization using the minimum set formulation of the reserve selection problem.

min_set_solution(
  name,
  dataset,
  settings,
  theme_data = settings$get_theme_data(),
  weight_data = settings$get_weight_data(),
  include_data = settings$get_include_data(),
  boundary_data = dataset$get_boundary_data(),
  gap = 0,
  boundary_gap = 0.1,
  legend_color = "#FF0000",
  cache = cachem::cache_mem()
)

Arguments

name

character name for new solution.
dataset

Dataset object to store the solution.
settings

SolutionSettings object with settings.
theme_data

Matrix::sparseMatrix() containing the theme data. Defaults to being automatically calculated from settings.
weight_data

Matrix::sparseMatrix() containing the weight data. Defaults to being automatically calculated from settings.
include_data

Matrix::sparseMatrix() containing the include data. Defaults to being automatically calculated from settings.
boundary_data

Matrix::sparseMatrix() containing the boundary data. Defaults to being automatically extracted from dataset.
gap

numeric relative optimality gap value. Defaults to 0.
boundary_gap

numeric value used to control the level of spatial clustering in the solution. Defaults to 0.1.
legend_color

character legend color.
cache

cachem::cache_mem() object used to cache intermediate calculations. Defaults to an empty cache such that (effectively) no cache is used.

Value

A Solution object containing the solution.
